  "texts": [
    "Among the spatially informed methods, methods that use graph convolutional frameworks (GCN) including SpaGCN, DeepST, STAGATE, and SEDR, generally achieved better performance than others, indicating the superior ability of GCNs to integrate spatial information.",
    "When it comes to the usage of histological information, stLearn, SpaGCN, and DeepST employed the H&E image of the spots, but their performance was not outstanding, suggesting the limited utility of image information, which is potentially due to the low quality of the images.",
    "Additionally, the image processing step is inefficient in terms of running time and memory usage, especially for highresolution images.",
    "This can make such methods unsuitable for larger spatial transcriptomics data as such data are growing in availability and scale.To explore the robustness of SEDR and competing methods with respect to hyperparameters, we tested the top 3 methods, namely SEDR, STAGATE, and DeepST (Fig. 2) with a varying number of nearest neighbors (K), which determines the level of local spatial smoothing.",
    "There was a slight fluctuation of ARI scores for all 3 methods on the 12 DLPFC sections with different K values (Additional file 1: Fig."
  ]
